From: XR1710G-YYH-OC Builder <builder@xr1710g.local>
Date: 2026-07-13
Subject: [PATCH] feeds: add luci-theme-argon feed

The OC overlay enables luci-theme-argon (patch 003 adds it to the
device DEFAULT_PACKAGES and the config seed selects it), but the
official OpenWrt feeds do not ship a third-party Argon theme.

Add jerrykuku/luci-theme-argon as a dedicated feed so that
`./scripts/feeds update -a` + `./scripts/feeds install -a` makes the
package visible to `make defconfig`.  The repo contains only the single
luci-theme-argon package (no other packages, no conflicts with stock
feeds).

The theme Makefile includes $(TOPDIR)/feeds/luci/luci.mk, which is
already available after the luci feed is updated, so no extra
preparation is needed.
---
--- a/feeds.conf.default
+++ b/feeds.conf.default
@@ -6,3 +6,4 @@
 #src-git targets https://github.com/openwrt/targets.git
 #src-git oldpackages http://git.openwrt.org/packages.git
 #src-link custom /usr/src/openwrt/custom-feed
+src-git argon https://github.com/jerrykuku/luci-theme-argon.git
-- 
2.43.0
